# Hok Item

Hok Item is a simple API allowing consumers to view all current hok items, hokd items from history, as well post new ones.

## Item List [/my_items]

### List All User Items [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "publishedAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z",
                "myItems": [
                //Each status depicted below
                    {
                        "itemId": 02350,
                        "itemStatus": "submitted for review"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02599,
                        "itemStatus": "posted for loan"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02412,
                        "itemStatus": "loan offered"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02689,
                        "itemStatus": "loan accepted"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02856,
                        "itemStatus": "loan repayed"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 01689,
                        "itemStatus": "loan faulted"
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
        
### Create a New Item [POST]

You may post a new item using this action. It takes multiple JSON objects.

+ Request (application/json)

         {
            "category": "electronics",
            "itemDescription": "brand new iPad2",
            "manufacturer": "apple",
            "manufactureYear": "2015",
            "modelName": "iPad 2 2nd generation",
            "condition": "brand new",
            "otherComments": "electronics",
            "loanDesired": "$250",
            "finalLoanAmount": "nil"
            "itemStatus": "posted for loan"
            "itemPics": {
                "server/img/01845_1/hockd.png",
                "server/img/01845_2/hockd.png",
                "server/img/01845_3/hockd.png"
                }
            
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /my_items/2

    + Body

            {
                "publishedAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z",
                "itemId": 02385,
                "category": "electronics",
                "itemDescription": "brand new iPad2",
                "manufacturer": "apple",
                "manufactureYear": "2015",
                "modelName": "iPad 2 2nd generation",
                "condition": "brand new",
                "otherComments": "electronics",
                "loanDesired": "$250",
                "finalLoanAmount": "nil"
                "itemStatus": "posted for loan"
                "itemPics": {
                    "server/img/01845_1/hockd.png",
                    "server/img/01845_2/hockd.png",
                    "server/img/01845_3/hockd.png"
                    }
            }
        
        
## Active Item List [/active_items/{active_items_id}]

+ Parameters
    + active_items_id (integer) - ID of the user's active items in the form of an integer
    
    
### View the user's active items [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "publishedAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z",
                "myItems": [
                    {
                        "itemId": 02350,
                        "itemStatus": "submitted for review"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02599,
                        "itemStatus": "posted for loan"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02412,
                        "itemStatus": "loan offered"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 02689,
                        "itemStatus": "loan accepted"
                    }
            ]
        }
        

## User Item History List [/history_items/{history_items_id}]

+ Parameters
    + history_items_id (integer) - ID of the user's history items in the form of an integer
    
    
### View the user's active items [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "publishedAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z",
                "myItems": [
                    {
                        "itemId": 02856,
                        "itemStatus": "loan repayed"
                    }, {
                        "itemId": 01689,
                        "itemStatus": "loan faulted"
                    }
            ]
        }
        


